news.title: Hong Kong court adjourns Shimao Group's liquidation petition until August 12
news.para: Many Chinese property developers are facing liquidation lawsuits by creditors since the sector slipped into a debt crisis in 2021, with a handful, such as industry giant China Evergrande Group, ordered to be liquidated.

news.title: China's Zhengzhou city allows developers to sell new homes at reduced prices
news.para: "The housing regulator no longer guides the sales price of new homes, and developers set their own prices for sales," the regulator's notice said.

news.title: Ambuja Cements posts profit of Rs 789.63 crore in Q1 Fy25
news.para: Ambuja Cements' revenue from operations was at Rs 8,311.48 crore during the June quarter compared to Rs 8,712.90 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal.

news.title: Omaxe may challenge Sebi order barring company, chairman, MD from securities market
news.para: ​The Sebi order had a negative impact on Omaxe's share prices. The stock of the company on Wednesday declined 4.99 per cent to Rs 152.20 apiece -- its lower circuit limit -- on the BSE.

news.title: Godrej Properties' profit jumps over four-fold to Rs 520 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: The total income grew to Rs 1,699.48 crore during April-June period of 2024-25 fiscal from Rs 1,265.98 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: House is a house, can't be an asset: Revenue secretary on indexation benefits
news.para: Revenue Secretary, Ministry of Finance clarified that the rollover benefits will continue on capital gains of up to Rs 10 crore under the new structure.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces' net profit drops 44% to Rs 5 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces bookings for the quarter grew 49% to Rs 201 crore, while collections stood at Rs 248 crore, up 21% from a year ago, the company said in a release.

news.title: Yamuna Expressway authority set to renew its bid to acquire 36 land parcels
news.para: Initiated in 2012, over 6,317 hectares of land were to be acquired across 36 villages, according to official data. Much of this land is in various blocks of Sectors 12, 14, 15, 16, 17, 18, 21, 22, 23, and 24.

news.title: Mumbai: Mhada gives offer letters to 158 residents of cessed buildings, waives NOC fee
news.para: The function was held at the housing agency's headquarters in Bandra East. Mhada said applicants must fulfill the conditions mentioned in the offer letter and take possession.

news.title: JSW joins the race to buy CK Birla's Orient Cement
news.para: The development sees the entry of a third contender for OCL’s 8.5 million tons per annum (MTPA) capacity after the Adani and Aditya Birla groups, both of which have been in active discussion with Delhi-based CK Birla at various points since late last year when JP Morgan kicked off the sale process.

news.title: Ghaziabad's circle rate set for a 20% hike, its first revision in two years
news.para: A higher circle rate means those buying houses will have to pay more in stamp duty, which will effectively increase the overall property prices.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 46 acre land in Indore
news.para: The development on this land will primarily comprise plotted residential units and will offer an estimated saleable area of ~1.16 million sq ft.

news.title: Macrotech Developers' profit jumps 2.7 times to Rs 475 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Total income grew to Rs 2,918.3 crore during the April-June period of this fiscal year from Rs 1,671.8 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding year.

news.title: Mindspace REIT's net operating income up 9% to Rs 496 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Net Operating Income (NOI) increased 9 per cent to Rs 496 crore, from Rs 455 crore a year-ago, while distribution grew 5 per cent in the reported quarter to Rs 299 crore, from Rs 285 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Sand will be made available for free for poor in state: Jharkhand CM
news.para: "Several issues related to sand such as its unavailability for the poor and its high prices and impact on Abua Awas Yojana have come to our notice. I would like to inform the House that our government will make sand free for non-taxpayers in the state," he said.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust's net operating income up 7% to Rs 413 crore in Q1FY25
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing, the company said it achieved retail Net Operating Income (NOI) of Rs 371.9 crore in April-June period of this fiscal, up 8 per cent from the year-ago period.

news.title: MMRDA tells HDIL to hand over 1,400 flats in Kurla buildings, Rs 35 crore in rent arrears
news.para: The notices were issued to the resolution professional of HDIL, a developer from the city facing insolvency proceedings, to hand over the 1,336 residential units and 50 commercial units in two buildings of Premier Compound in Kurla.

news.title: Carlyle to sell upto 6.4% stake in PNB Housing Finance for Rs 1,256 crore on July 30
news.para: According to a term sheet issued by IIFL Securities, Quality Investment Holdings, an entity of Carlyle, will sell 1.66 crore shares at a floor price of Rs 775 apiece, aiming to raise Rs 1,256 crore.
